      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 28
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting a mechanically sound 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant equipped with VarioCam Plus. This example is optimized for the enthusiast, featuring a G96 6-speed manual transaxle with precise shift gates and a refreshed clutch assembly. Crucially, the IMS bearing has been retrofitted with a dual-row ceramic solution, and the Rear Main Seal (RMS) was replaced concurrently. The suspension retains its factory-spec damping characteristics with multi-link rear geometry providing excellent mechanical grip. Recent service includes a low-temperature thermostat installation and a cooling system flush to mitigate bore scoring risks. While the exterior shows minor road patina, the drivetrain remains tight, delivering linear torque and a visceral flat-six acoustic profile. A driver-grade 911 that prioritizes performance and mechanical longevity over showroom perfection.",
